    <Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CIV5_DAWN_VIVALA_METIS_TEXT">
      <Text>Greetings, Louis Riel, father of Manitoba and leader of the Métis. Your people emerged from the collision of two worlds, granting you a wholly new spirit of strength and ingenuity. With that spirit, your people spread across the breathtaking North American wilderness, and helped build a trade network that stretched from sea to shining sea. As your Old World predecessors turned to conquer Métis lands, you, Louis Riel, rose to defend them by pen and sword not once, but twice. While you met your end at the conclusion of your second rebellion, your sacrifice inspired others to champion the rights of the Métis and the First Nations for generations.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]The Métis are blessed with the culture of two worlds. Now they require a leader to push them beyond the greatness of their ancestors. Louis Riel, will you once more fight for the legacy of your people? Will you build a civilization that will stand the test of time?</Text>
    </Row>
